    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-26T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-26T09:00:00-05:00" n="872"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">661.1115/69: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-26T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 26—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>848. My 514, March 27, noon [<hi rend="italic">10 a.m.</hi>], and previous
                    correspondence. Foreign Office now replies to memorandum of March 27th and
                    states that British Government cannot at present see its way to propose
                    legislation or to initiate other steps to provide that there should be returned
                    to the rightful owners, before trade is resumed between Great Britain and
                    Russia, such gold or securities as the Government of the Soviet may have
                    illegally acquired. Persons claiming to be rightful owners will, however, be
                    enabled to institute such legal action as is possible for the protection of
                    their property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
